  "prompt": "Why does Quora do this \"marked as needing improvement?",
  "response": "Quora marks content as \"needing improvement\" for several reasons, typically related to the quality and clarity of the answer provided. Here are some common factors that can lead to this designation:\n\n1. **Lack of Clarity**: The answer may be unclear or difficult to understand, which can hinder readers from grasping the main points.\n\n2. **Inadequate Depth**: Answers that do not provide sufficient detail or fail to thoroughly address the question may be flagged. Readers generally expect comprehensive responses.\n\n3. **Inaccuracy**: If the information provided is incorrect or misleading, it may be marked for improvement to encourage corrections or more accurate explanations.\n\n4. **Relevancy**: Sometimes, answers may stray off-topic or include irrelevant information, which can lead to them being labeled as needing improvement.\n\n5. **Formatting Issues**: Poor organization, lack of structure, or excessive jargon can also contribute to an answer being flagged, as these can make the content harder to read and comprehend.\n\n6. **Lack of Sources**: Answers that claim facts or statistics without providing sources or references may be seen as less trustworthy, prompting a need for improvement.\n\nBy marking content as needing improvement, Quora aims to maintain a standard of quality and provide users with reliable, clear, and useful information. This feedback can encourage contributors to refine their answers and enhance the overall quality of the platform.",
